                <li><strong>Less caffeine dependence</strong> - Natural energy replaces artificial stimulants</li>
                <li><strong>Better evening energy</strong> - Still have energy for family and hobbies</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>Why This Gets Worse After Age 40</h2>

        <p>If you're over 40, you've probably noticed the afternoon crash getting worse over the years. There's a scientific reason for this:</p>

        <p><strong>NAD levels decline by approximately 50% between ages 40 and 60.</strong> Your cellular power plants are literally running out of fuel as you age.</p>

        <p>This is why younger people might bounce back from an afternoon slump, but as you get older, the crash becomes more severe and lasts longer.</p>

